President Obama, Secretary of Defense Robert Gates, and General David Petraeus met to discuss the progress of the military surge in Afghanistan, the growth of the Afghan National Security Forces, and President Karzai's upcoming announcement on transitioning to Afghan security lead. They also discussed the plan to start reducing U.S. forces in July and the timeline for Afghanistan to take full responsibility for security by the end of 2014. A photo of the meeting can be found at the provided link.